x4freetext: Pelletron facility
The products of the reaction were momentum
analysed by the the spectrograph and detected by a
500-mu-m-thick surface barrier position-sensitive
detector (PSD), with an area of 47 x 8 mm2, positioned
on the focal plane. During the experiment, elastically
scattered ions of 6Li were continuously monitored by
a surface barrier detector fixed at 27.5 degr. (lab.)
Relative normalization of the inelastic cross sections
was obtained from the number of elastically scattered
particles detected by the monitor during each run. The
absolute normalization, for each isotope, was obtained
from the fit of optical model predictions to the
experimental elastic angular distributions, measured on
the same target and under similar conditions.
Maximum scale uncertainties  are estimated,
when contributions due to target nonuniformity and
statistics in the elastic data are also considered.
